# Copy to steam-gamescope.env (same directory) to tune the LightDM "Gamebian Steam (gamescope)" session.
# Debian + hybrid laptop: Mesa NVK often cannot run gamescope; prefer AMD RADV for the compositor.
# ICD filename differs by Mesa (check: ls /usr/share/vulkan/icd.d/ — often radeon_icd.json vs radeon_icd.x86_64.json):
#GAMEBIAN_VK_ICD_FILENAMES=/usr/share/vulkan/icd.d/radeon_icd.json
#
# Or pick a device explicitly (see `gamescope --help` → --prefer-vk-device):
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_EXTRA_ARGS=--prefer-vk-device <value>
#
# If gamescope hangs on startup with NVIDIA in the mix:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_DISABLE_WSI=1
#
# Kiosk fills gamescope -W/-H from xrandr when unset (upstream default without them is often 1280x720 —
# Steam gamepad/Big Picture can look tiny in one corner). To force manual size only:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_NO_AUTO_WH=1
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_WH="-W 1920 -H 1080"
#
# Toggle gamescope fullscreen at runtime if needed: Meta/Super+F.
#
# "Switch to Desktop" (gamescope IN_GAMESCOPE): steamos-session-select desktop → Openbox in the
# current LightDM login only (does not change next boot). Re-enable kiosk: steamos-session-select
# gamescope or sudo gamebian-enable-steam-lightdm-session (steam-for-linux #11241).
#GAMEBIAN_STEAM_NO_STEAMOS3=1

# Older workaround (nested gamescope under X): BPM in corner unless -W/-H set on the outer session.
# If kiosk fails to start after an update, revert nested mode:
#GAMEBIAN_GAMESCOPE_KIOSK_EMBED=1
